-- Turkish Assets Held by Foreigners Reach Record, Dunya Reports
-- B y   S e l c u k   G o k o l u k
-- 2012-08-23T06:16:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-23/turkish-assets-held-by-foreigners-reach-record-dunya-reports.html
Turkish assets held by foreigners
including stocks and bonds reached a record high at 
$126.8 billion as of Aug. 3, Dunya newspaper reported,  citing  
central bank, government and stock exchange data.  Foreign investors have added $31.9 billion to their
holdings of Turkish assets via so-called ``hot money" inflows so 
far this year, the Istanbul-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Selcuk Gokoluk in Istanbul at 
 sgokoluk@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
